The People’s Democratic Party (PDP) has said Engr. Abba Kabir Yusuf remains its candidate for today’s governorship election in Kano State. The Director Media and Publicity of the PDP Presidential Campaign Organisation, Mr. Kola Ologbondiyan said in a statement yesterday that the Court of Appeal last Thursday, restrained INEC from removing Engr. Abba Yusuf from the list, as the governorship candidate of the PDP. Mr. Ologbondiyan said the decision of the court has put to rest all controversies regarding the PDP candidate for the election. “The Court of Appeal is commended for delivering justice by upholding the lawful nomination of Engr. Abba Yusuf as the PDP candidate for the Kano state governorship election. “All stakeholders are advised to note the order of the Court of Appeal and be guided accordingly,” the party said. PDP hails court judgment on its Kano governorship candidate Court dismisses case against Kano PDP guber candidate Court dismisses case against Kano PDP gov’ship candidate